æ–º. –ß—Ç–æ–±—ã —Å–¥–µ–ª–∞—Ç—å —Ñ–æ—Ä–º—É –∞–≤–∞—Ç–∞—Ä–∫–∏ —á–µ—Ç—á–µ -- –¥–µ–ª–∞—é –æ–±–≤–æ–¥–∫—É. \r\nMacBook-Pro-14_---3.svg\r\n\r\n–ü—Ä–æ–±—É—é –ø—Ä–∏–∫–∏–Ω—É—Ç—å –∫–∞–∫ –±—É–¥–µ—Ç –∂–∏—Ç—å –∏–∫–æ–Ω–∫–∞ —Å –ø–æ—Å—Ç–æ—è–Ω–Ω—ã–º —Ü–≤–µ—Ç–æ–º –Ω–∞ —Ä–∞–∑–Ω—ã—Ö —Ñ–æ–Ω–∞—Ö. \r\nMacBook-Pro-14_---7.svg\r\n\r\n–í—ã–≥–ª—è–¥–∏—Ç –Ω–µ–µ—Å—Ç–µ—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω–æ, —Ç–æ–≥–¥–∞ —Ä–µ—à–∞—é –∫—Ä–∞—Å–∏—Ç—å –∏–∫–æ–Ω–∫–∏ —Ü–≤–µ—Ç–æ–º —Ñ–æ–Ω–∞ –Ω–∞ 2 —Ç–æ–Ω–∞ —Ç–µ–º–Ω–µ–µ. –ó–∞—Ä–∞–Ω–µ–µ –æ–ø—Ä–µ–¥–µ–ª—è—é —ç—Ç–∏ –æ—Ç—Ç–µ–Ω–∫–∏ \r\nMacBook-Pro-14_---6.svg\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n# –ù–∞–±–æ—Ä –æ–∫–æ–Ω—á–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã—Ö –∏–∫–æ–Ω–æ–∫ –¥–ª—è –∞–≤–∞—Ç–∞—Ä–∫–∏.\r\nAvatar_random-image.svg\r\n\r\n# –ò—Ç–æ–≥\r\n1) –ë–µ—Ä–µ–º –≥–æ—Ç–æ–≤—ã–π –Ω–∞–±–æ—Ä –∏–∫–æ–Ω–æ–∫\r\n2) –ù–∞–±–æ—Ä background-color, \r\n3) –ù–∞–±–æ—Ä icon-color, –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–π –∑–∞–¥–∞–Ω –∫ –∫–∞–∂–¥–æ–º—É —Ñ–æ–Ω—É \r\n4) –ì–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∏—Ä—É–µ–º –∞–≤–∞—Ç–∞—Ä–∫—É\r\n\r\n# –ü—Ä–∏–º–µ—Ä—ã\r\nEmpty-1.svg\r\nEmpty-2.svg\r\nEmpty-3.svg\r\nEmpty.svg', '', 'neasden', 'generaciya-avatarok', 'a:10:{i:0;s:11:\"Empty-1.svg\";i:1;s:11:\"Empty-2.svg\";i:2;s:11:\"Empty-3.svg\";i:3;s:9:\"Empty.svg\";i:4;s:23:\"Avatar_random-image.svg\";i:5;s:23:\"MacBook-Pro-14_---2.svg\";i:6;s:23:\"MacBook-Pro-14_---3.svg\";i:7;s:23:\"MacBook-Pro-14_---7.svg\";i:8;s:23:\"MacBook-Pro-14_---6.svg\";i:9;s:23:\"MacBook-Pro-14_---1.svg\";}', '1', '0', '1', '1', '1667664762', '1669278084', '10800', '0', '1', '0', '67', '0', '0', '', '', ''), ('59', '1', 'Interface transformation', 'Gradually, from the MVP stage, we are approaching a full-fledged release of the product, so we are rebuilding the interface and saturating it with details. I go through the flow and see where we got fails in the user\'s path. \r\n\r\nFor example, we did not complete the flow or overlooked the situation where a double pop-up happened. \r\n\r\nWe have finished branding and soon the landing page will be launched. It remains only to match the platform with a new style.\r\n\r\nI will show a few examples of what it means to ‚Äúsaturate the interface‚Äù.\r\n\r\n# Projects\r\nAt the MVP stage, the ‚ÄúProject page‚Äù was nominal, we did not interact with it, we just wrapped fuzzers in it.\r\n\r\ninterface-transformation.png\r\nIt was like this. This is the real screen from my account on the platform. I don\'t bother with names :)\r\n\r\n\r\nWe have redesigned the ‚ÄúAll projects‚Äù page. The \"Deleted\" tab turned into the \"Bin of projects\" link.\r\n\r\n\r\nAllProject.svg\r\nIt has become.\r\nWe pasted an intermediate page \"Project\" between the \"All projects\" page and the \"Fuzzers\" page. \r\n\r\nThe Project is a new page, on which users will administer it. They will be able to monitor the capacities in the project, manage all the fuzzers from one page, and monitor their status and state. In the future, users will be able to transfer fuzzers from one project to another.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nProjectList_Selected-Items-1.svg\r\nIntermediate page view ‚Äì Page Project\r\n\r\n\r\nAnother example:\r\n\r\n# Integrations\r\nIntegrations are settings for notifications about the status of the fuzzer, its crashes, and other important events of the project. \r\n\r\nYou can set up a project so that all notifications for it will fall directly to Jira or Youtrack.\r\nThis page didn\'t exist before. All needs for it were closed by a drawer (haha, pun).\r\n\r\ninterface-transformation-1.png\r\nSo, choose a task tracker, give access and everything will work.\r\n\r\nThe platform didn\'t have \"All integrations\" page. It was believed that one Integration was enough. But user cases have shown the opposite. Some people need several integrations: so that the bot writes in Telegram if something happens, for example, the fuzzer stops.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIntegration-2.svg\r\n\r\nWe added \"All integrations\" page. Now the project can contain several integrations. Users can turn them on/off, edit and make two-way integration -- this is when some tasks for a fuzzer can also sent from Jira.\r\n\r\n\r\n# New system pages\r\nWe have added system pages. There users can change their passwords, set up system notifications in the application, and switch to another tariff plan if there is not enough capacity\r\n\r\nPlans.svg\r\nNotification.svg\r\nSecurity-&-Login.svg\r\n\r\n\r\n# Style\r\nWe have changed platform colors to new ones, the font to a corporate one, and added illustrations to the pages of empty states.\r\n\r\nLog-in.svg\r\nEmpty-6.svg\r\nEmpty-10.svg\r\nEmpty-8.svg\r\nEmpty-9.svg\r\n\r\n\r\n# Problems\r\nDuring the usability testing, several problems were found:\r\n\r\n1. We don\'t have keyboard navigation at all. This is a big disadvantage for our users. We are thinking about how to implement it now. The advantages of mouseless are well described ((https://habr.com/ru/company/netcracker/blog/273071/ here (in Russian) ))\r\n\r\n\r\n2. The problem of identifying an icon without a label. A question of semantics, for example, the edit icon was indicated by a gear, although its function was purely editorial.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n# More details:\r\n\r\n((https://bondifuzz.com/ See Project Page))\r\n((https://www.notion.so/1a71264deb63410ba2055a4ac00b7bdf?v=3d26fe54c79047159b5aba5abf93eea8 Learn Design Guidelines))', '', 'neasden', 'interface-transformation', 'a:16:{i:0;s:28:\"interface-transformation.png\";i:1;s:14:\"AllProject.svg\";i:2;s:30:\"interface-transformation-1.png\";i:3;s:9:\"Plans.svg\";i:4;s:16:\"Notification.svg\";i:5;s:20:\"Security-&-Login.svg\";i:6;s:11:\"Empty-4.svg\";i:7;s:11:\"Empty-5.svg\";i:8;s:10:\"Log-in.svg\";i:9;s:11:\"Empty-6.svg\";i:10;s:11:\"Empty-7.svg\";i:11;s:11:\"Empty-8.svg\";i:12;s:11:\"Empty-9.svg\";i:13;s:12:\"Empty-10.svg\";i:14;s:32:\"ProjectList_Selected-Items-1.svg\";i:15;s:17:\"Integration-2.svg\";}', '1', '0', '1', '1', '1664185897', '1669278096', '10800', '0', '1', '0', '113', '0', '0', '', '', ''), ('60', '1', 'Why Error messages isn\'t secure', 'Error message is a way of informing the user of important changes in a prominent way.\r\n\r\nWhen we design interfaces, we rarely think about error messages. After all, we are remembering about it. We highlight the error, display a message, and nudge users toward the correct input. \r\n\r\n\r\n**For user: **clear error message is good\r\n**For business** error messages can make or break the experience in situations when things go south, especially if they struggle with high abandonment.  A good error message reduces the burden on technical support and staff. A good error message allows you to maintain trust in the service in a difficult moment\r\n\r\n**But, to security clear message about error is potential for hacking.**', '', 'neasden', 'why-error-messages-isnt-secure', 'a:0:{}', '0', '0', '1', '0', '1664123232', '1664446484', '10800', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '', '', ''), ('61', '1', 'License plates', 'On vacation, I saw many license plates from other countries. Each country has its requirements and laws for license plates. \r\n\r\n# Austria\r\nThe text is in black letters and numbers on a white background. The common design includes a blue section on the left with the EU Circle of Stars and Country Code (A), like other EU vehicle registration plates. \r\n\r\nOn the top and bottom, there are red-white-red tri-bands, the national colors of Austria. \r\n**SZ -- code of town, Salzburg**\r\nPXL_20220816_112519455.jpg\r\n\r\nThe green license plates belong to electric car\r\nPXL_20220816_105649038.jpg\r\nPXL_20220815_103835537.jpg\r\n\r\n\r\n# Germany\r\nThe distinctive feature of German license plates is the use of a special font and umlauts. As well as the use of land stickers and technical inspection stickers, which are attached directly to the registration plate. \r\n\r\nModern German plates use a typeface called ((https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FE-Schrift FE-Schrift)) Its monospaced letters and numbers are slightly disproportionate to avoid fakes and to improve machine readability. The font looks very cool.\r\n\r\nPXL_20220816_110503210.jpg\r\n\r\nPXL_20220816_110500677.jpg\r\n\r\nPXL_20220816_110137789.jpg\r\n\r\nSee, how different license plates from Italy and Germany\r\n\r\nPXL_20220816_140302674.jpg\r\n\r\n# the Netherlands\r\nThe text is in black **plastic** letters and numbers on a yellow background.\r\n\r\nNowadays the letters used do not include vowels, to avoid profane or obscene language. To avoid confusion with a zero, the letters C and Q are also omitted and letters M and W are not used because they are too wide. \r\nPXL_20220816_110228332.jpg\r\n\r\n# Poland\r\nThe license plates are invalid without hologram stickers placed on the license plates.\r\n\r\nPXL_20220816_110316107.jpg\r\n\r\nPoland allows custom plates\r\nlicence-plates.png\r\n((https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vehicle_registration_plates_of_Poland  ))\r\n\r\n# Slovakia\r\nUsed standard latin alphabet  -- 24 letters, excluding Q, W and Slovak letters such as ≈†. Germany solved the wide-letters problem makes own font. Why not do the same?\r\nPXL_20220816_141906032.jpg', '', 'neasden', 'licence-plates', 'a:11:{i:0;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_112519455.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_105649038.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"PXL_20220815_103835537.jpg\";i:3;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_110503210.jpg\";i:4;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_110500677.jpg\";i:5;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_110137789.jpg\";i:6;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_140302674.jpg\";i:7;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_110228332.jpg\";i:8;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_141906032.jpg\";i:9;s:18:\"licence-plates.png\";i:10;s:26:\"PXL_20220816_110316107.jpg\";}', '1', '0', '1', '1', '1664960577', '1664960827', '10800', '0', '1', '0', '84', '0', '0', '', '', ''), ('62', '1', '–ó–∞–¥–∞—é –≤–æ–ø—Ä–æ—Å—ã –∏ —Å—Ç—Ä–æ—é —Ñ–ª–æ—É', '–ö–∞–∫-—Ç–æ —É –º–µ–Ω—è –±—ã–ª–∞ –∑–∞–¥–∞—á–∞ –ø–µ—Ä–µ—Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∞—Ç—å —Ä–∞–∑–¥–µ–ª –ø—Ä–æ —Ä–∞—Å—à–∏—Ä–µ–Ω–∏—è –∏ –æ–±–Ω–æ–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏—è, –∏ –ø—Ä–µ–¥–æ—Å—Ç–∞–≤–∏—Ç—å –Ω–∞–∏–±–æ–ª–µ–µ —É–¥–æ–±–Ω—ã–π, –ø–æ–Ω—è—Ç–Ω—ã–π –∏–Ω—Ç–µ—Ä—Ñ–µ–π—Å. + –ü—Ä–æ–¥—É–º–∞—Ç—å —Å—Ü–µ–Ω–∞—Ä–∏–∏ —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∫–∏, –æ–±–Ω–æ–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏—è, —É–¥–∞–ª–µ–Ω–∏—è 